Remarks. The distribution range of
A.christofferseni
is extended by approximately five degrees south from the type locality (Atol das Rocas, ~3°51”S,
). The current southernmost record of the species is Praia dos Carneiros, Tamandaré, Pernambuco (~ 8°41’S ). Furthermore, the bathymetric distribution increased significantly considering the collection of a specimen at 51 m depth. The specimens from Pernambuco (female and male) resemble the holotype . However, some morphological variations between the two specimens from Pernambuco and the holotype were observed, such as the exopod of the third maxilliped (
) reaches the penultimate segment of the endopod (vs. not reaching the penultimate segment of the third maxilliped in the holotype ); telson (
) with mesial spiniform setae 4.5 times longer than the lateral spiniform setae (vs. mesial spiniform setae twice the size of the lateral spiniform setae in the holotype ); third and fourth pereiopods (
) armed with four spiniform setae along the ventral margin and a pair of distal spiniform setae (vs. five spiniform setae and a pair of distal spiniform setae in the holotype ).
